#
#   Field 1: Non-zero field
#   Field 2: A decimal field value
#
# Detailed description
# [1-9][0-9]{0,}
#   [1-9]: This matches a single digit from 1 to 9 (i.e., any non-zero digit).
#   [0-9]{0,}: This matches zero or more occurrences of any digit (0-9).
# [0-9\.]{1,}$:
#    This matches one or more occurrences of either a digit (0-9)
#    or a literal dot (.). The {1,} quantifier means one or more digits.
#    $: This is an anchor that matches the end of the line.
#
